The electrochemical behavior of battery assemblies according to an embodiment and those not according to an embodiment is shown in FIGS. 1 to 5. It shows the
FIG. 1 the result of a Li plating/stripping experiment of a cell assembly not according to an embodiment as a function of time;
FIG. 2 the result of galvanostatic cycling of a cell assembly not according to an embodiment as a function of time;
FIG. 3 the result of a Li plating/stripping test once of a cell assembly not according to an embodiment and once of a cell assembly according to an embodiment with a dual salt electrolyte as a function of time;
FIG. 4 the result of galvanostatic cycling of a cell assembly not according to an embodiment and a cell assembly according to an embodiment with a dual-salt electrolyte as a function of time;
FIG. 5 the result of a mechanical stability test, once of a cell structure not according to an embodiment and once of a cell structure according to an embodiment, as a function of the pressure deflection.
